  "plainText": "Pure Brilliance\nObject Info\n40\nSource\nDropped by\nCrafting\nDescription\nTransmute Infused Moon Shards into Pure Brilliance.\n×3 ( only)\nFilters\n(for ).\nMiscellaneous\n\"purebrilliance\"\nExclusive to:\n“It's blinding me with science!”\n–Wilson\n“It's pretty, but it'll never beat fire.”\n–Willow\n“Little rocks are too bright!”\n–Wolfgang\n“It hurts my eyes.”\n–Wendy\n“IT IS... PERFECTION...”\n–WX-78\n“Pure energy, in a crystalline form.”\n–Wickerbottom\n“Makes me feel a bit twitchy.”\n–Woodie\n“I wonder if she knows about this...”\n–Maxwell\n“Like staring up intö the spötlights...”\n–Wigfrid\n“It's blinding our poor spider eyes!”\n–Webber\n“My, I've never seen anything shine so brightly.”\n–Warly\n“Ahhh. Pretty.”\n–Wormwood\n“I ain't dazzled by much, but that'll do it.”\n–Winona\n“Hyuyu, it tickles my impish brain!”\n–Wortox\n“Glurgh, too bright!”\n–Wurt\n“That's gotta be the shiniest rock I've ever seen.”\n–Walter\n“If only I could use it to power one of my watches... Oh well.”\n–Wanda\nPure Brilliance is a resource exclusive to Don't Starve Together, introduced in From Beyond. It is obtained by mining Ryftstals that spawn from Lunar Rifts.\nPure Brilliance is used to craft the Brightsmithy and all of the items craftable at said station.\nWilson with the Lunar Innovator Skill can craft 1 Pure Brilliance with 3 Infused Moon Shards, as well as use 1 Pure Brilliance to craft 2 Infused Moon Shards.\nUsage[edit | edit source]\n×5\n×5\n×4\n×4\n×4\n×2\n×4\n×4\n×6\n×3\n×6\n×4\n×3\n×2\n×2\n×3\n×3\n×5\n×3\n×8\n×5\n×3\n×3\n×3\n×2\n×4\n×2\n×20\n×3\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nPure Brilliance was introduced in the Taking Root update.\nThe opposite of this item is Pure Horror.\nPure Brilliance is a play on words as the word Brilliance pertains to both high intelligence and intense luminescence.\nAssets[edit | edit source]\nIdle animation\nResourcesCraftable Items\nView or edit this template\nResources\nAttention: The following categories are only for the p